    <briefdescription>
<para>LwM2M resource item structure. </para>
    </briefdescription>
    <detaileddescription>
<para>Value type must match the target resource as no type conversion are done and the value is just memcopied.</para>
<para>Following C types are used for resource types:<itemizedlist>
<listitem><para>BOOL is uint8_t</para>
</listitem><listitem><para>U8 is uint8_t</para>
</listitem><listitem><para>S8 is int8_t</para>
</listitem><listitem><para>U16 is uint16_t</para>
</listitem><listitem><para>S16 is int16_t</para>
</listitem><listitem><para>U32 is uint32_t</para>
</listitem><listitem><para>S32 is int32_t</para>
</listitem><listitem><para>S64 is int64_t</para>
</listitem><listitem><para>TIME is time_t</para>
</listitem><listitem><para>FLOAT is double</para>
</listitem><listitem><para>OBJLNK is struct <ref refid="structlwm2m__objlnk" kindref="compound">lwm2m_objlnk</ref></para>
</listitem><listitem><para>STRING is char * and the null-terminator should be included in the size.</para>
</listitem><listitem><para>OPAQUE is any binary data. When null-terminated string is written in OPAQUE resource, the terminator should not be included in size. </para>
</listitem></itemizedlist>
</para>
    </detaileddescription>
